title: Coco‚Äôs Conclusion: Truly Painless, High Quality
text:
[[VIDEOID:b35db5602af2156947967b6b6850e6d3]] I have used a few different IPL machines over the years. This one is the first painless one I have had.
Everything is packaged well and comes in a nice case. The machine itself is very easy to use. Once you turn it on, it automatically turns on a cooling mechanism that makes it more pleasant on the skin and less likely to overheat, I would imagine. I would recommend that you read the directions or watch a video on how to operate it. It has different settings that you can change by clicking the right button. There is also a long or short area function on this which is very nice, making it so you can drag the device down a longer area, like a leg, while pressing the button.
The directions say to use the device want to eat for 12 weeks and after that, as needed. I will update the review if sufficient hair removal has not happened at this point in time, but I‚Äôm already noticing that I have to shave less.

title: Great nail polish, healthy and effective
text:
I am a huge fan of this brand of nail polish. I started using them due to toenail fungus, and a stubborn fingernail fungus -- thanks to gel polishes from the nail salon. I discovered Dr's Remedy polishes a couple of years ago, and have totally switched to this brand. They are also good if you have aging, yellowing nails. The polish clears that up -- especially if you consistently use their base coat first.

If I have any complaints or suggestions, I would say that they need to add more shades -- especially shades in the neutral family. Some nudes, darker beiges, etc. The khaki shade is a nice neutral but a bit too pale;, and the few sheer shades they offer are very nice for long-lasting daily wear. I do wish there were more sheer shades -- and maybe a sheer lavender shade that would help combat the yellowed appearance of the nail. But otherwise, this is a wonderful, healthy product and the polish lasts quite a while.

title: Extremely hydrating but lightweight. Does have essential oils & fragrant ingredients though
text:
This comes with no outer product box, just the bottle. But, the bottle is sealed with plastic wrapping around it. It is made in the US. The ingredients are listed on the label.

This is supposed to be cruelty free, gluten free, silicone free, sulfate free, paraben free, talc free, 100% vegan, and have clean ingredients. It didn‚Äôt have any labels on it saying it was cruelty free, but the brand‚Äôs website said they‚Äôre cruelty free. It also said they use natural and organic ingredients. But, they are not certified organic. It states, ‚ÄúOur products are made with natural and organic ingredients, however, they are not certified organic. All of our products are made in the U.S. using top-quality domesticated and imported ingredients.‚Äù I‚Äôm not surprised they said they‚Äôre not certified organic. I love their honesty. I‚Äôve seen lots of skincare brands claim their products are 100% organic when they definitely aren‚Äôt. Most skin care products are water-based and water can NOT be certified as organic, so the possibility of finding a 100% organic skincare product is close to impossible.

This claims to be hydrating, brightening, and soothing. It claims to target fine lines around the eyes, reduce appearance of dark circles and puffiness, and hydrate the eye area. It claims the key ingredients are triple peptides, bergamot oil, and citric acid. I included a full ingredient list at the end of my review (marked with üü£). I included some info on some of the ingredients before that (marked with üü¢).

This comes in a nice pump bottle. The pump does squirt out too much if you‚Äôre not careful. I find if I carefully press it so I‚Äôm not pushing it down all the way, I get enough product and don‚Äôt waste any. It‚Äôs a thin gel consistency. It glides on nicely. It absorbs quickly leaving my under eyes feeling really hydrated and smooth. I have pretty dry under eyes. If I apply concealer, I have to make sure to moisturize them really well so they don‚Äôt look dry and cakey. A lot of the moisturizers that hydrate my under eyes enough are thicker and end up being too heavy to use concealer over. This is PERFECT! It‚Äôs thin and lightweight, but feels extremely hydrating! It gives my under eyes enough hydration and plumps them up. It doesn‚Äôt leave a sticky residue at all. Concealer goes over it beautifully and looks nice and smooth.

I haven‚Äôt been using it long enough to say anything about how it works long term on dark circles, firming, etc. But, I can say it‚Äôs really hydrating and plumping if you‚Äôre looking for something extremely hydrating under the eyes. I‚Äôm hopeful for other benefits long term given the ingredients, but even if I don‚Äôt get any more benefits, I‚Äôm still loving how well it hydrates my under eyes while being so lightweight! Just keep in mind it does have some essential oils and fragrant ingredients in it, so if you have sensitive skin, you might want to avoid this or at least check the ingredient list to see if they‚Äôre things that you‚Äôre sensitive to.

üü¢Info on ingredients
Saccharide Isomerate, which is a 100% natural and plant-derived moisturizer. It binds to the skin stronger and longer than other moisturizer ingredients do so it can keep skin hydrated longer than usual.

Palmitoyl Tripeptide-1 & Palmitoyl Tetrrapeptide-7 - These are peptides combined to create a compound called Matrixyl 3000. Matrixyl is a highly-effective peptide composition that has been shown to stimulate the production of collagen and elastin, fill in fine lines & wrinkles while restoring elasticity.

Sodium Hyaluronate, which is a form of hyaluronic acid (HA). Helps skin hold onto water, making skin more plump and elastic.

Acetyl Hexapeptide-8 (aka Argireline), which is called ‚Äúnatures Botox.‚Äù It is a synthetic peptide that has several different potential wrinkle-fighting and anti-aging effects. It's so effective, that experts say it's the closest thing to Botox you can get. It prevents the muscle movement that leads to wrinkle formation. Argireline also promotes collagen production and optimizes the function of collagen, which both fight fine lines and improve moisture levels in the skin. It‚Äôs good for anyone looking to smooth wrinkles caused by repeated muscle movement in areas such as the forehead and around the eyes.

Chamomilla Recutita (Matricaria) Flower Extract, which has great anti-inflammatory properties and antioxidant properties.

ESSENTIAL OILS, PERFUMING INGREDIENTS
It has some essential oils and perfuming ingredients in it - Bergamot Fruit Oil, Orange Oil, Linalyl Acetate, Geranyl Acetate, and Linalool. These are super common and cheap fragrance ingredients. They oxidize on air exposure and the result can be quite irritating to the skin and can lead to allergic contact dermatitis and they count as frequent skin sensitizers. It is best to avoid them if you have sensitive skin.

üü£FULL INGREDIENT LIST
Water, Glycerin, Butylene Glycol, Saccharide Isomerate, Palmitoyl Tripeptide-1, Palmitoyl Tetrapeptide-7, Sodium Hyaluronate, Acetyl Hexapeptide-8, Chamomilla Recutita (Matricaria) Flower Extract, Carrageenan, Citrus Aurantium Bergamia (Bergamot) Fruit Oil, Citrus Aurantium Dulcis Oil, Sclerotium Gum, Xanthan Gum, Carbomer, Polysorbate 20, Potassium Sorbate, Citric Acid, Sodium Citrate, Triethyl Citrate, Linalyl Acetate, Geranyl Acetate, Terpineol, Linalool, Phenoxyethanol, Ethylhexylglycerin.

title: Powerful! It‚Äôs in the joules rating!
text:
I‚Äôve tried so many at home IPL devices and have gotten hair removal at salons. The thing you need to check for is the power of each laser. For instance many cheap IPL will say there joules rating is between 2-6 joules typically. At salons it varies but it‚Äôs typically between 20-50 joules. And that means the higher the joules usually the better the results or faster because it‚Äôs actually hitting the hair with that higher power.

This IPL device has 5 levels between 6-20 joules. That is typically as high as you‚Äôll find for at home IPL devices. So at the highest level you‚Äôll get the low end of salon quality laser removal.

Be very careful with the higher levels though, just because it can reach that power doesn‚Äôt mean it will be the best result for your skin. So be careful, follow directions and make sure to not damage your skin

title: Reduced redness & hydrating, but need ingredient list in ENGLISH!
text:
This comes in a nice outer product box. Made in Korea. The brand‚Äôs website said it‚Äôs 100% vegan, excluding animal ingredients and animal experiments. It also doesn‚Äôt include parabens.

It comes in a nice compact. It‚Äôs a compact like a cushion foundation where you open it and there‚Äôs a kind of lid that holds the sponge applicator, and you lift that lid to reveal the product. You press the applicator sponge into it (or your own sponge or brush) and then apply it. The brand‚Äôs website said the included sponge applicator is an ‚Äúeco puff‚Äù made of ‚Äúeco-friendly corns‚Äù and is ‚Äú99.9% anti-bacterial and water-repellent,‚Äù which makes it safe on skin and keeps puff clean.

This is a liquidy but balm kind of texture. It isn‚Äôt as thick as a balm. It just feels like a cushion foundation. But this isn‚Äôt a foundation. It has a very light, mint green color to it. It‚Äôs so light that it‚Äôs almost white but has the green color to it. When applied, it reduces redness. It doesn‚Äôt do as well as my more pigmented green correctors, but it does a nice job while being hydrating and lightweight on the skin. It‚Äôs something that works well before applying foundation. It is lightweight enough to wear well under foundation. It isn‚Äôt a primer really, it doesn‚Äôt smooth out the skin or fill in pores. But, it does reduce the redness in my skin so then I use less foundation and concealer. If you have a TON of redness or it‚Äôs REALLY red, this might not be enough since it isn‚Äôt extremely pigmented. But, it will make a difference. I like it isn‚Äôt drying on the skin either.

I‚Äôm just not sure how I feel about it though. It works well on the skin. But, I do like to know what‚Äôs in my products. I don‚Äôt like that they provided barely any product info, and the ingredients on the product box weren‚Äôt in English. They also didn‚Äôt include them here on the product page. Not even the product photos provided any real info on the product - what it does, who it‚Äôs for, how to use it, ingredients, etc. I had to go to the brand‚Äôs website to find out more. Yes, it‚Äôs a simple Google search, but it‚Äôs not really something you should have to do.

Normally, I would just go to the brand‚Äôs website to find the list of ingredients when they‚Äôre not included on the Amazon product page. But, the Jung Saem Mool website didn‚Äôt have them on their website either. I looked for them elsewhere and did find an ingredient list on Korean Beauty Box, but didn‚Äôt think they were accurate because they didn‚Äôt include centella asiatica, pine sprout, or green calamine powder, which are supposed to be in this product. So, I translated the ingredients from the box myself. But, I‚Äôm not that confident in the ingredients provided on the box.(I included a photo from the box, and also included the ingredients at the end of my review in English)

It doesn‚Äôt seem like a complete list of ingredients to me. It has the first ingredient as titanium dioxide. It has tocopherol (vitamin E) as the 3rd ingredient. The rest of the ingredient are 7, kind of versions I‚Äôd guess you‚Äôd call them, of centella asiatica. There‚Äôs nothing else listed. It‚Äôs kind of odd. The brand‚Äôs website said this is supposed to have ‚Äú2 plants - pine sprout containing fresh moisture and centella asiatica roots.‚Äù I saw the ‚Äúcentella asiatica roots‚Äù in the ingredients when I translated them. But didn‚Äôt see any ‚Äúpine sprout.‚Äù I also saw something about ‚Äúcica pine water‚Äù on the brand‚Äôs website, but again, not sure what that‚Äôs supposed to be? The brand‚Äôs website also mentioned ‚ÄúNatural green calamine powder covers reddened skin tone.‚Äù Again, I didn‚Äôt see any calamine powder at all in the ingredients.

The 7, I guess versions, of Centella Asiatica are:
Centella Asiatica Extract (5,159,235ppm) - Well known soothing, antioxidant, and moisturizing ingredient. Anti-inflammatory. The main biologically active components are Asiaticoside, madecassoside, asiatic acid, and madecassic acid. All of which are in this.

Centella Asiatica Leaf Extract (0.035ppm)

Centella Asiatica Root Extract (0.03ppm)

Madecassoside (0.0025ppm) - One of the main biologically active components of Centella Asiatica.

Madecassic Acid (0.0025ppm) - One of the main biologically active components of Centella Asiatica.

Asiaticoside (0.0025ppm) - One of the main biologically active components of Centella Asiatica.

Asiatic Acid (0.0025ppm) - One of the main biologically active components of Centella Asiatica. It‚Äôs less prominent than it‚Äôs sister component, Asiaticoside, but it still contributes to the well-established moisturizing and wound healing abilities of Centella Asiatica.

Overall, it works well. It reduces my redness, feels hydrating on the skin, and works well on its own and under foundation. It feels lightweight on the skin. If they provided the full ingredient list, it would be something I‚Äôd be willing to purchase. But, right now, I don‚Äôt like they didn‚Äôt include them and don‚Äôt like that they can‚Äôt even be found online as far as I could tell. And I just have a hard time believing the ingredient list I translated from the box is the full ingredient list. I don‚Äôt know. If the ingredients aren‚Äôt a big factor for you, this is nice and works well. If knowing the ingredients are important to you, I‚Äôd look elsewhere. There‚Äôs other similar products that actually provide a full ingredient list, and a lot of them are far cheaper. I give it 3 stars.

How to Use (from brand‚Äôs website):
Use as last step of skin care routine. Dip puff into content and gently apply and dab on skin.

Special Tips (from brand‚Äôs website)
Carry it in makeup bag or purse for easy supply of moisture to skin when it dries up.
Use as lightweight skin tone corrector to correct sensitive skin tone covered by masks instead of applying heavy, caking makeup.

FULL INGREDIENTS
Ingredients | Titanium dioxide (CI 77891], Centella Asiatica Extract (5,159,235ppm), Tocopherol, Centella Asiatica Leaf Extract (0.035ppm), Centella Asiatica Root Extract (0.03ppm), Madecassoside (0.0025ppm), Madecassic Acid (0.0025ppm), Asiaticoside (0.0025ppm), Asiatic Acid (0.0025ppm)

**NOTE: Just for reference, 1ppm = 0.0001% (or 10,000 ppm = 1%). So‚Ä¶

Centella Asiatica Extract (5,159,235ppm) = 515.9235%
*5,159,235ppm is parts per million, so it means there‚Äôs 5,159,235 parts of Centella Asiatica in one million molecules
Centella Asiatica Leaf Extract (0.035ppm) = 0.0000035%
Centella Asiatica Root Extract (0.03ppm) = 0.000003%
Madecassoside (0.0025ppm) = 0.00000025%
Madecassic Acid (0.0025ppm) = 0.00000025%
Asiaticoside (0.0025ppm) = 0.00000025%
Asiatic Acid (0.0025ppm) = 0.00000025%

title: Superb Bakuchiol cream
text:
This is a lovely Bakuchiol cream. Bakuchiol is a fantastic natural alternative to retinol. It‚Äôs safe for sensitive skin and pregnant women! It‚Äôs not photosensitive (unlike retinol) so it can be used both am and pm. The packaging of this product feels simple yet luxurious. The glass jar packaging reminds me a lot of herbivore products.

This cream is lovely to use. It is a thicker heavier cream so, it does take a little longer to absorb. It‚Äôs non greasy and although it is a thick cream it does feel light weight once applied. As the cream absorbs it does give a nice radiant dewy glow to my skin tone. I can easily see how this cream would help with anti aging and fine lines with repeated daily use. I‚Äôve been using this cream for about almost a week now and I love seeing my skin so well nourished and hydrated.

The ingredients in the cream are delightful. There is one ingredient that I always acknowledge. This cream does use a silicone ingredient polysilicone-34. I honestly don‚Äôt know much about this silicone ingredient and it might be the first product I have used that includes this particular silicone. This cream is gentle and effective even for sensitive skin but I do always acknowledge silicones in the ingredient list. In the week I have used this cream I have not noticed any close comedones, millia or any other adverse side effects from adding this cream to my skin care routines.

I love how deeply nourishing, refreshed and hydrating this cream is for my skin. Even though it takes a while to absorb when I use this cream in the mornings its still easy to apply my make up once this cream does absorb. I don‚Äôt wear foundation most days but occasionally I do wear a finishing powder to even out my skin tone if need or to help blend out my highlighter or blush. This cream doesn't sit heavy on my skin or interfere with my make up application or longevity.

I am very happy with this cream and would absolutely recommend it to those who have sensitive skin (as long as you tolerate silicone okay), or to those who prefer a retinol alternative that can still yield good results.

title: Great spray foundation
text:
I have been using Jerome Alexander Airbrush spray foundation for a while now and enjoy it, so when this came up I knew I had to give it a try.

Normal liquid foundations feel very thick and seem to visibly sit on top of my skin. When buffed in with a kabuki brush, this blended very nicely. Shake the can well and spray directly onto the brush for the best results. I aim onto my shower just in case I accidentally overspray. Some people complain about the waste of the spray in these types of foundations. First, you should only be spraying about 3 inches away from your brush. Ny further and you risk missing the brush altogether. Second, I spray in short bursts. A little goes a long way, and I was impressed by the color match in this foundation. It holds up well and looks very natural.

title: Very full coverage
text:
When I ordered this there were only two shade choices, fair light and medium. I am a light neutral usually so I chose fair light. It is too light for me but not so light that I can't make it work with bronzer. The instructions say to spray it on their brush then apply it. I wanted to spray it directly on my face so I did and it is the most immediate full coverage application I've ever had. You do need to be careful because you could end up with it in your hair and whatnot. I also sprayed it on my sponge and applied it like that. It worked fine that way but it wasn't as full coverage.
This takes a while to dry down and if you're like me and don't set your face this could be a problem when you're applying the rest of your makeup. I did feel like my contour and bronzer was removing the foundation somewhat. Once it dried down completely though it stayed. The finish seemed more matte to me than satin but I have dry skin so that could be why. I think this is a really nice foundation but it takes some work. Also I seriously hope they do something about the shade range.

title: Soothing oil/serum
text:
Each of the isfrom blends seems to have a recommended time of day for usage. Greenery is to soothe you for a peaceful afternoon. Of course, it can be used anytime as needed
The concept behind this three-oil blend is to soothe body mind and soul, using Hemp seed oil to soothe the skin, Bergamot oil to soothe the mind and the visually calming green imparted by the Holy Basil oil to soothe the spirit.
The oil feels, silky, the fragrance is light and balanced, all three oils combining to create a mellow scent. The ingredients are natural, organic, and ecofriendly.
The directions encourage you to make this a moment. Specifically, after cleansing and toning, drop the oil into the palm, inhale to stimulate the senses and tap your skin gently until the oil is absorbed.
A few drops provided good coverage and after patting it in, took a little while to sink in. It never felt sticky, or heavy, just a light silky layer that once absorbed left my skin feeling soft and nourished.
The care taken in producing this is apparent, even to the presentation. This is a beautiful oil and the 1 oz bottle should last a long time.

title: One-Step Magic Straightening Perm Kit
text:
I have semi-curly but puffy hair that I need to tame at least once every 3-4 months. Otherwise, I have to straighten my hair every day to look decent. I have been using this Japanese product which is a 2-step for the straightening and neutralizing. It usually takes a total of 3 hours or more to go through the entire process, with 45 mins session for each treatment steps and then the drying and straightening hair in between. I was really intrigued with the one-step because it saves so much time.

The order comes with magic straightening kit to do at home. There are instruction manuals in both Korean and English. It gives you step by step instructions that are very clear and easy to follow. The bottle already comes with the treatment. All you need to do it apply. Before you do this, there are hair treatment packets to use prior and after the treatment to protect your hair from excessive damage. The kit also comes with plastic cover for your shoulders and a brush for application.

I applied it over the top area because my hair is pretty long and really you should only target the new hair growth if you've done the treatment previously. If it was my first time I probably would not have enough treatment for my long hair. I would need to order two.

The instruction states to check after 10 minutes. Every hair is different so you will have to assess if you need to leave it on longer. The instruction specifies the duration and also guides you on how to check if your hair is ready to be washed out. If you pull one strand and you notice the curls are gone, then it's probably time to wash them. I left mine on for 40 minutes. I don't recommend it but I needed to from past experience because my hair is crazy. You rinse out the treatment but it tells you not to rub them. Just wash them through gently with your fingers. I applied the hair mist after washing it out, because you can feel the hair stiffen. Then I proceeded to blow dry and straighten the hair.

I washed my hair again after 2 days and sure enough the treatment worked. I do feel that because of the dryness, I still need to straighten the hair some, but definitely better than having to sit every morning and straighten the entirety of the hair.

For an avid magic straightening perm treatment user, I do recommend the product. I suggest getting additional product to make sure you revive your hair after treatment.

title: Pleasant But Feels More Clarifying Than Hydrating To My Dry Skin-Has Risky Ingredient TEA
text:
I have dry, sensitive and mature (55+) skin and used this Reboncel Aqua Rich Foaming Cleanser daily for about a week. This cleanser has fragrance that smells relatively light to me, though fragrance is an ingredient that poses health risks. I generally avoid foaming face cleansers as they tend to make my skin overly dry, but this has a pleasing creaminess and initially made my skin feel good. It cleaned my skin well yet left it feeling refreshed, soft and comfortable after use.

After using this wash more than a few days in a row, it felt more clarifying (better for oily skin) than hydrating to my skin. While it didn‚Äôt strip my skin or make it visibly irritated, by the end of the week my skin just didn‚Äôt feel as comfortable as it did at first and it felt like my skin would end up too dry if I continued daily use. So I switched back to my creamy, hydrating cleansers, but felt this cleanser would still be good to use as needed as a clarifying cleanser.

However, while this wash has some good ingredients such as Centella Asiatica, Aloe Extract and Sodium Hyaluronate, this has controversial Triethanolamine (‚ÄúTEA‚Äù) high on the ingredient list. It‚Äôs on my personal list of ingredients to avoid after reading many articles about it and seeing it on lists of risky chemical by many sources. Some sources say it‚Äôs safe in amounts we get thru cosmetics, but I‚Äôm concerned about the cumulative effect of risky chemicals.

TEA is a nitrosamine used to generate foam and adjust pH and is likely a hormone disrupter and irritant. But the bigger issue for me is that TEA gets absorbed through the skin and reacts with other chemicals to form the carcinogen NDEA. While less risky in rinse off products, it still poses more risk than I‚Äôm comfortable with. The problem is that I have no way to know if this cleanser or any product I‚Äôm using with it has chemicals that react with TEA.

So, for me, I find it best to avoid all products with TEA, especially since so many alternative products are available that don‚Äôt have it. I also dislike that this has so much Cocamidopropyl Betaine (second ingredient), which I generally avoid mostly due contamination concerns. Fragrance also poses health risks, though it‚Äôs a common ingredient I don‚Äôt avoid altogether (but I do try and minimize use). All things considered, this is just okay for me. 3 stars.

title: Nice bronzer but don‚Äôt like the highlighter
text:
This comes in an outer product box. It‚Äôs made in China. The tube this comes in is nice. It has a matte look to it.

The contour stick was what really interested me in this set. So many cream contour sticks labeled as ‚Äúcontour‚Äù end up being really warm toned. Contour is supposed to mimic your natural shadows, so it‚Äôs supposed to be cool toned, even grey toned. But, it‚Äôs hard to find one that‚Äôs actually cool toned, and even harder finding one that‚Äôs grey toned. This one looked like it was neutral, leaning cool with a kind of rosy undertone. So, I wanted to give it a try. The few rosy/pink toned contour/bronzer sticks I‚Äôve found have worked well for me as bronzers because I have neutral leaning slightly cool skin.

On me, thus leans more warm toned than I‚Äôd like. But, once blended out, it isn‚Äôt as orange as others. Of course, it could be different for you, depending on your undertone. While it doesn‚Äôt work as a contour for me like it wanted, it does make a nice bronzer for me. The formula of it is nice. It‚Äôs soft, smooth, creamy. It blends easily. I never swipe sticks like these onto my face. I always take my sponge or brush, dab it onto the stick, and then blend it onto my skin. I find that works better and I don‚Äôt need to worry about whether swiping it directly on will lift my foundation underneath. This is pigmented, but it blends out so easily that it‚Äôs easy to blend it away. I find if I pick up and apply a little, it blends out easily and looks natural on my skin but I just need to be careful not to blend it away! But, I can also build it up for a more intense color. I like that. Once blended out, it is matte and dries down to a powder like finish that I don‚Äôt need to set and it lasts all day without any issues.

The highlighter is okay. It‚Äôs too glittery for my liking. I like more of a pearl look without glitter. But if you don‚Äôt mind micro glitter, you might like this. Its really subtle aside from the glitter so I just think there‚Äôs better options.

Overall, I think it‚Äôs worth it for the contour/bronzer side. It works really well and is easy to work with (when dabbing your brush/sponge onto the stick and then applying it) and it sets down on its own with a matte powder like finish without needing to be set. I wouldn‚Äôt recommend the highlighter. It‚Äôs just really sheer other than glitter so I think there‚Äôs better options. But, if you like a sheer but glittery highlighter, then this could work for you. I give it 4 stars because I really like the bronzer, I just don‚Äôt like the highlighter.

text:
I am very unimpressed with this jade roller. Upon ordering I thought this would be a lovely addition to my skin care routines. I thought I could use it for depuffing, to help increase product absorption or simply to apply a little massage oil before using my myofascial tools. I‚Äôm not even entire sure I can utilize this..

First the roller part detaches from the lid easily. On unboxing and just checking out the tool I placed the cap back on the tool and then when i went to remove it for first use the roller ball came right off the top. It took me about 15 minutes to be able to twist lock the rolled ball back to the lid. (First photo) Once I got the roller ball re attached and tried to place ice in the main compartment I found you cant get regular shaped ice in. Only broken ice will fit into the packaging. Secondly, the first time I place ice in it the roller was not cold at all what so ever. I actually had to place ice, let it melt and then place a second round of fresh ice in it for the roller ball to actually get cold. Thirdly, it has no fluid control at all what so ever. So when using this with ice or if the ice melts at all it will just profusely leak water all over where ever you‚Äôre applying it. So that rules out me being able to use this with massage oil.

I do like the size of the jade roller and I feel like the concept is there it just needs better packaging. I can‚Äôt say I would recommend this because it feels cheap. There‚Äôs better jade roller options on the market that would provide better consistency with use, effectiveness and results.

title: Not Sure What to Think
text: Around 6 months ago, we adopted our first goldendoodle. I had heard that their fur was higher maintenance so I researched what we would need to best take care of him. I ended up ordering a big slicker style brush and this one. When we first got him, his fur was badly matted and he wasn't used to being brushed at all. We slowly got him used to being brushed and now we regularly use the slicker brush on him. This brush however, really pulls at his fur. I might have been tempted to think that it was just not the right brush for his fur, but on a recent attempt to trim his fur myself (rather than take him to the groomers) I found that I really needed this brush to get his curls combed out enough for the clippers to easily get through. It is incredibly slow going to even get through a small patch of his fur using this, let alone his entire body (he's medium/large). I'm thinking that we may just need to stick to the professional groomer for most haircuts and I'll just stick to the in-between appointment trims. So maybe it's me or maybe it's this comb or? The other issue I have with this comb is that the actual comb part comes apart from the wood handle. It's not ideal, but it does go back together and it's able to be used, so...?

title: Soothing & Skin Feels Less Sensitive, Hydrates & Improves Skin Texture, Free Of Fragrance/Alcohol
text:
Skin & Lab Barrierderm Milky Serum Milk Ceramide Complex is a milky serum free of fragrance and alcohol that comes in an easy to use dropper bottle. Ceramides can make skin healthier by strengthening the skin barrier, preventing moisture loss and protecting against environmental damage. Also, ceramides work better combined with certain types of ingredients that are contained in this serum, such as cholesterol, glycerin, squalane (rich in fatty acids) and more.

This serum feels wonderful on my dry, sensitive and mature (55+) skin that needs a lot of hydration and is aggravated easily by chemicals fragrance, natural fragrancing essential oils and extracts, drying alcohol, aggressive products, the environment and so on. I‚Äôve been using this ceramide serum after cleansing and follow with my face cream, but it also layers well with my favorite staples, such as a Vitamin C and hyaluronic acid serum (followed by my moisturizer).

I like that this ceramide serum doesn‚Äôt appear to have any harsh ingredients, and it feels soothing and gentle to my skin. I‚Äôve used it about a week so far and it adds noticeable hydration that isn't heavy, greasy or sticky, and my normally sensitive skin is calm and comfortable. Also, my skin texture feels soft and seems more elastic. I can‚Äôt judge the full benefits yet as that can take many weeks or months, but I‚Äôm pleased so far and will keep using this serum. title: CGM friendly, minty scent
text:
Let me start by saying that the pump came broken, which is unfortunate. However, I was still very excited to try this shampoo because of the great ingredients.

I have been following the Curly Girl Method (CGM) for more than 2 years and I have seen great results with my hair. So I am very strict when choosing hair care products avoiding parabens, sulfates, drying alcohol, non-water soluble waxes. This shampoo does not have any of those 'bad ingredients' and love seeing Aloe Vera is the very first ingredient since it is a great ingredient in general.

It does clean the scalp nicely, leaving a minty sensation. It is important to call out that since it does not have sulfates (which is the most common ingredient in regular shampoo to clean the scalp but can be harsh), you will need to scrub your scalp a bit more with your fingers tips (this is the same with any sulfate free shampoo).

Overall rating due to broken pump: 4.5 rounding up to 5

Full Ingredient List: Aloe Barbadensis (Organic Aloe Vera) Leaf Juice*, Rosa Centifolia (Organic Rose Hydrosol)* Flower Water, Sodium Cocoate (Saponified Coconut) Oil, Vegetarian Glycerin, Plant Cellulose, Citrus Aurantium Sinensis (Orange) Fiber, Coffea Arabica (Green Coffee) Leaf/Seed Extract, Caffeine, Mentha (Mint) Extract, Rice Ferment Filtrate (Sake), Biotin, Vitamin B3, Vitamin B6, Extracts of Camellia Sinensis (Organic Green Tea) Leaf*, Panax Ginseng (Ginseng) Extract, Lavandula Angustifolia (Lavender) Flower/Leaf/Stem, Mentha (Mint) Essential Oil, Lonicera Caprifolium (Japanese Honeysuckle), Acetum Mali (Apple Cider Vinegar), Curcuma Longa (Tumeric) * Certified Organic

title: Gentle, Soothing Moisture
text:
Being that my facial skin changes greatly during the winter months, I thought this serum might help to re-establish some moisture while battling my winter dryness. This review is for: [SKIN&LAB] Barrierderm Milky Serum | Infused with Milk Ceramide Complex, Squalane, and Panthenol to ...

I have used products from Skin & Lab before and liked most of them, and this serum is no exception. I was coming off of a different moisturizer that really irritated my skin, so I introduced this serum slowly. I started using it only once a day and once that previous irritation cleared up I moved up to twice a day.

This serum is somewhere in between watery and a cream. The glass bottle is opaque and the serum does dispense as milky-looking. It has no scent that I can detect. The dropper dispenses enough for about half my face, so I've been using two droppers per application. It has soothed my skin, clearing up my previous Rosacea break out and smoothing out my skin. I have an oily t-zone and a super dry chin this winter, and all of that seems to be gone now.

Due to these cold, breezy winter months, I have been using a moisturizer over this serum. I suspect that in the summer months, I might not even need to do that.

I'm looking forward to continued use of this product and when it's gone I will most likely buy more. The price is affordable and this works wonderfully on my dry, winter skin.

text: The smell is more strawberry rhubarb but it's like a facial cream in texture. Ultra smooth going on. You can feel the moisturizing as you use this. Zero irritation on sensitive skin. Highly giftable. Great packaging, durable, tight lid container.  Ample product so it's a great value for the money. You can use it with your fav scrubby for enhanced sensation and exfoliating. Leaves skin clean and glowing. Skin feels nourished, refreshed. Good stuff!!!

title: Pretty Good Quality üßë‚Äçü¶±
text:
I received one pack of "Disposable Face Towels".

I use facial towels like this daily for my facial care routine. I find it easier to just use one facial towel each time for washing & then rinsing my face (so the same facial towels gets rinsed out multiple times under running water). That's compared to the alternative of using a new clean wash cloth every single time multiple times a day.

These facial towels are White in color & have a circle / dot type of pattern. They are also a decent size, big enough to cover my palm & I found them easy to hold / work with. They have no scent.

They seem to hold up fairly well even when using them with facial products that contain alcohol or other stronger types of ingredients.

title: Super cute for bridesmaid gift bags
text:
I ordered these Satin Bridesmaid Scrunchies in the green color and it's a really pretty sort of sage-green, just like the pictures. They're a nice silky-feeling satin, and the elastic bands inside feel strong and aren't too thin or flimsy.

I've gotten satin scrunchies that are just as nice MUCH cheaper than these, but these have the cute little "To have and to hold your hair back" tags on them so they're ready to gift to your bridesmaids. They'd be perfect in gift bags along with coordinating robes!

title: Great for Beginners! Pretty and Sparkly!
text: Current price $15.99. Great set for young people who are just starting to play with make-up. They will love the sparkly handles and pink brushes! Not a bad set but for $15.99 I think they do the job, plus look pretty. Mine did not have a lot of shedding. 4 Stars. Hope you find this review and pictures helpful! Not a professional set - but a good set for the price! Plus they are pretty! :) Nicely boxed for gifting! The bag could have been a bit nicer, but it works!

title: Pepper lotion
text: Love what this company is about, love the box, I even love the bottle this stuff comes in. The stuff .. not so much. As the name of the review reads, this stuff smells like pepper and some type of flower or flowers. The texture is SUPER oily honestly I only used one pump to remove some lipstick off my arm (skin test) and it was beyond too oily and didn't fully remove the lipstick. I only stopped because my skin was sensitive and I guess it doesn't like the mixture of this stuff so I rinsed with a warm cloth and was left with SUPER soft skin and an obvious makeup line. I recommend this as a moisturizing skin lotion not a makeup remover that and the smell are the only reason I'm deducting stars.

The only problem with this headband is that it is HIGH and thick. So, when you wear it, it looks kinda funny or off on top of your head. It reminds me of the puffy towel headbands my wife uses when washing her face. This is definitely one of those accessories that looks great until you try it on.

title: Title and description are a little misleading...
text: The wife and the MIL are huge fans of these face rollers, so we've tried just about every version and model out there. Although this does have a nice heavy, metal handle, the balls are PLASTIC. Stating in the title that it's a "Metal Facial Roller" is misleading because there are models where everything is indeed metal. In the description, it also says "our facial roller tool is High quality metal material". Ummmm... that's JUST THE HANDLE. The models we've tried with plastic balls had the fake metal paint water off, and some of them even crack after a while, so this is important in determining quality of the tool and the price that it should command. Most of the ones with plastic are priced around $8-10, while the all metal ones are $24-30. That being said, the price of this one might seem like a good deal if you think it's an all metal model - but it is actually overpriced for the plastic-ball-model.

I'm beyond thrilled to say it has the unique Moroccanoil product scent that not only smells lovely but actually lasts for a decent amount of time; a rarity with my hair!

title: Good conditioner
text: I use several different brand conditioners, cleaners and waterproofing sprays. This conditioner can be used on almost every leather except suede, Nubuck or rough out. It is wax based and oil based so it will darken the color of your leather a couple of shades. That said I did like it a lot, there is no weird smell it is easy to apply, it penetrates real well and pretty fast. The scuff covering is fair, it does make your leather water repellent not waterproof. Based on the characteristics of this conditioner I would use it on daily wear shoes, boots and leather goods. I would not use it much on work boots not that it is a bad product but for work boots I like stronger waterproofing qualities and I wouldn‚Äôt waste this good product on nasty dirty work boots. If you want to keep it safe and are bothered by Leather darkening a bit, use bick 4 a good safe product but it is a lighter conditioner and requires more frequent applications. If you are not bothered by the darkening of the leather and want a deep natural penetrating conditioner that works exceptionally well go for this one. By the looks of it I will keep it as my top conditioner for most of my footwear. I will try some of their other  products.

title: Too heavy for fine hair but amazing for thick hair‚Ä¶
text: This was too heavy for my fine thin hair, it left it looking greasy. My daughter has thick beautiful hair and this conditioner was perfect for her. She has highlights in her hair and they‚Äôve stayed bright since using this conditioner.

title: It's kind of muddy, and the smell is earthy
text:
The first impression of this, it feels more like a natural clay-ish, almost like a mud for facials consistency rather than the typical shampoo-like beard wash you might be accustomed to.

The scent is subtle, it's kind of earthy. Not a perfumed or heavy scent.

It lathers up pretty much like other kinds of soap or shampoo and rinses off clean.

It doesn't leave a sticky or slick residue.It's fine as a beard wash. I didn't feel like my beard was any more soft or easy to manage.

It's an alright beard wash, not one that I was excited about. If you like more earthy and natural feeling personal wash ingredients, you might like it more.
